Invocation Name: preventive health
des:
Preventive Health Care Services is an informational resource and a tool to get personalized preventive services recommendations. Preventive health services, are a set of essential screenings, tests and vaccinations that all insurance plans must cover without charging you anything, even if you have a deductible.

The actual eligibility or to accurately determine when the preventive health services are effective for a particular health plan, or for eligibility, one must contact the health plan or organization that administers that program.

Content Credit: Personalized preventive services recommendations are sourced from "myhealthfinder". The myhealthfinder tool is maintained by the Office of Disease Prevention and Health Promotion (ODPHP) in collaboration with the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ).

The skill is not produced by or affiliated with any U.S. Federal agencies.
priv: The developer reported that this skill does not collect personal information.
